	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98882536774189><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5696&mid=98882536774189>Cha doesn't affect mez at all</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5696&mid=98882536774189#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 2nd 1:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a lvl 60 chanter on Xev and have a couple things to say regarding this robe and the posts I've seen.<br><br>Whoever says that AC is nothing to caster is full of crap because I notice a MASSIVE difference between when I DON'T wear my AC gear (roughly 580 AC) and when I don full bore AC items (roughly 770 AC)&nbsp;&nbsp;AC makes the difference between getting hit and not getting hit.  AGI does nothing, and dex makes no difference in regaining concentration.<br><br>As for charisma helping with mez...mez is a set duration spell and is not affected in any way by charisma.  Dazzle (lvl 49 mez) has a duration of 96 seconds.  Glamour of Kintaz (lvl 54 uber mez) has a duration of around 26 seconds.  Rapture (59 uber mez) is also about 25 seconds.  Charisma only affects charm.  In my experience cha has also helped mem blur but that's probably just my imagination.<br><br>Either way.  It's my opinion that how a robe looks is more important than stats.  A few extra int/cha here n there aren't worth looking like a doofus.  So if this robe is ugly...bah!<br><br>Kaelyn "The Fashion Crusader" Shields<br>60th Phantasmist of Xev<br>Looks are everything!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
