	   <tr><td colspan=2>That reasoning assumes that the AGI(X) is a static multiplier.&nbsp;&nbsp;From my delving into the formulas (and no, I don't have any "evidence" to post here, so you can either believe me or not ;) the AGI factor is not a static multiplier but a formula instead, based on level, current agi, and defense skill.  Oddly enough, it has nothing to do with race... an Ogre would get the same AC from AGI that a Gnome would.  Go figure.<br><br>If it is indeed a formula, what you posted works except: (AC-BaseAC)/AGI=X<br>If it is a static multiplier, what you posted works fine as is.  Not overly useful, unless you want to figure out how much AC per AGI you're getting, but nice nonetheless.<br><br>Wow, has this thread gone OT or what?!<br>&nbsp;<br>Vdian Valdis &lt;Sword of Fate&gt;<br>"The pointy end goes in the other person"</td></tr>
