	   <tr><td colspan=2>I must, therefore i will.&nbsp;&nbsp; As i see the above message, i'm reminded of all the people who have never played a chanter, who, for some reason, want to tell me how to play mine.  After 52 levels, i think i can safely say, most of these people need to simply shut that hole below their nose.<br><br>THE job of a chanter is crowd control.  Buffs are a nice addition, but make no mistake... not having clarity does not equal death as quick as 5 frogs in seb on the loose looking for someone to pummel.  <br><br>I've seen various people here making comments on wether cha helps mez/charm.  From personal experience, i find that it helps only marginally the chance for mex to stick in higher encounters (as in the afore mentions frogville).  It DOES NOT change the time mez lasts.  From personal exp, only large increases in cha seems to help with charm sticking.<br><br>As far as my job.... you better learn to play a chanter before you tell me my job; and, you better be a whole helluva lot better chanter than me if you expect me to listen.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Moraganth<br><br>The most convincing arguement for the existance of intelligent life elsewhere in the universe is that they haven't made contact with us. </td></tr>
